A former Head of State, General Yakubu Gowon (rtd) has kicked -off a free Hepatitis B screening and vaccination expressing concern over the high rate of infection in Adamawa State. The exercise was organised by the Yakubu Gowon Centre in collaboration with the Presidential Committee on North East (PCNI). Gowon who spoke at Specialist Hospital,Yola said he was disturbed that out of 5000 screened in January, 150 tested positive, saying the exercise was expected to control rate of prevalence in the state. The PCNI Coordinator, Bello HammanDiram, explained that many of the affected people could not afford treatment, stressing the need for government intervention to facilitate access.